home.tutorials.cefLogs.longDescription: This is a module for receiving Common Event Format (CEF) data over         Syslog. When messages are received over the syslog protocol the syslog         input will parse the header and set the timestamp value. Then the         processor is applied to parse the CEF encoded data. The decoded data         is written into a `cef` object field. Lastly any Elastic Common Schema         (ECS) fields that can be populated with the CEF data are populated.         [Learn more]({learnMoreLink}).

home.tutorials.common.premCloudInstructi:
Go to [Elastic Cloud]({link}). Register if you do not already have an account. Free 14-day trial available.

Log into the Elastic Cloud console

To create a cluster, in Elastic Cloud console:
 1. Select **Create Deployment** and specify the **Deployment Name**
 2. Modify the other deployment options as needed (or not, the defaults are great to get started)
 3. Click **Create Deployment**
 4. Wait until deployment creation completes
 5. Go to the new Cloud Kibana instance and follow the Kibana Home instructions

If you are running this Kibana instance against a hosted Elasticsearch instance, proceed with manual setup.

Save the **Elasticsearch** endpoint as {urlTemplate} and the cluster **Password** as {passwordTemplate} for your records

home.tutorials.gcpMetrics.longDescriptio: The `gcp` Metricbeat module fetches monitoring metrics from Google Cloud Platform using Stackdriver Monitoring API. [Learn more]({learnMoreLink}).
home.tutorials.gcpMetrics.shortDescripti: Fetch monitoring metrics from Google Cloud Platform using Stackdriver Monitoring API.
home.tutorials.golangMetrics.longDescrip: The `{moduleName}` Metricbeat module fetches internal metrics from a Golang app. [Learn more]({learnMoreLink}).
home.tutorials.golangMetrics.shortDescri: Fetch internal metrics from a Golang app.
home.tutorials.gsuiteLogs.longDescriptio: This is a module for ingesting data from the different GSuite audit reports APIs. [Learn more]({learnMoreLink}).
home.tutorials.haproxyLogs.longDescripti: The  module collects and parses logs from a ( `haproxy`) process. [Learn more]({learnMoreLink}).
home.tutorials.haproxyMetrics.longDescri: The `haproxy` Metricbeat module fetches internal metrics from HAProxy. [Learn more]({learnMoreLink}).
home.tutorials.haproxyMetrics.shortDescr: Fetch internal metrics from the HAProxy server.
home.tutorials.ibmmqLogs.longDescription: Collect IBM MQ logs with Filebeat. [Learn more]({learnMoreLink}).
home.tutorials.ibmmqLogs.shortDescriptio: Collect IBM MQ logs with Filebeat.
home.tutorials.ibmmqMetrics.longDescript: The `ibmmq` Metricbeat module fetches monitoring metrics from IBM MQ instances [Learn more]({learnMoreLink}).
home.tutorials.ibmmqMetrics.shortDescrip: Fetch monitoring metrics from IBM MQ instances.
home.tutorials.icingaLogs.longDescriptio: The  module parses the main, debug, and startup logs of [Icinga](https://www.icinga.com/products/icinga-2/). [Learn more]({learnMoreLink}).
home.tutorials.icingaLogs.shortDescripti: Collect Icinga main, debug, and startup logs.
home.tutorials.iisLogs.longDescription: The `iis` Filebeat module parses access and error logs created by the IIS HTTP server. [Learn more]({learnMoreLink}).
home.tutorials.iisLogs.shortDescription: Collect and parse access and error logs created by the IIS HTTP server.
home.tutorials.iisMetrics.longDescriptio: The `iis` Metricbeat module collects metrics from IIS server and the application pools and websites running. [Learn more]({learnMoreLink}).
home.tutorials.impervaLogs.longDescripti: This is a module for receiving Imperva SecureSphere logs over Syslog or a file. [Learn more]({learnMoreLink}).
home.tutorials.impervaLogs.shortDescript: Collect Imperva SecureSphere logs over syslog or from a file.
home.tutorials.infobloxLogs.longDescript: This is a module for receiving Infoblox NIOS logs over Syslog or a file. [Learn more]({learnMoreLink}).
home.tutorials.infobloxLogs.shortDescrip: Collect Infoblox NIOS logs over syslog or from a file.
home.tutorials.iptablesLogs.longDescript: This is a module for iptables and ip6tables logs. It parses logs received         over the network via syslog or from a file. Also, it understands the prefix         added by some Ubiquiti firewalls, which includes the rule set name, rule         number and the action performed on the traffic (allow/deny).         [Learn more]({learnMoreLink}).
home.tutorials.juniperLogs.longDescripti: This is a module for receiving Juniper JUNOS logs over Syslog or a file. [Learn more]({learnMoreLink}).
home.tutorials.juniperLogs.shortDescript: Collect Juniper JUNOS logs over syslog or from a file.
home.tutorials.kafkaLogs.longDescription: The `kafka` Filebeat module parses logs created by Kafka. [Learn more]({learnMoreLink}).
home.tutorials.kafkaLogs.shortDescriptio: Collect and parse logs created by Kafka.
home.tutorials.kafkaMetrics.longDescript: The `kafka` Metricbeat module fetches internal metrics from Kafka. [Learn more]({learnMoreLink}).
home.tutorials.kafkaMetrics.shortDescrip: Fetch internal metrics from the Kafka server.
home.tutorials.kibanaLogs.longDescriptio: This is the Kibana module. [Learn more]({learnMoreLink}).
home.tutorials.kibanaMetrics.longDescrip: The `kibana` Metricbeat module fetches internal metrics from Kibana. [Learn more]({learnMoreLink}).
home.tutorials.kubernetesMetrics.longDes: The `kubernetes` Metricbeat module fetches metrics from the Kubernetes APIs. [Learn more]({learnMoreLink}).
home.tutorials.kubernetesMetrics.shortDe: Fetch metrics from your Kubernetes installation.
home.tutorials.logstashLogs.longDescript: The modules parse Logstash regular logs and the slow log, it will support the plain text format and the JSON format. [Learn more]({learnMoreLink}).
home.tutorials.logstashLogs.shortDescrip: Collect Logstash main and slow logs.
home.tutorials.logstashMetrics.longDescr: The `{moduleName}` Metricbeat module fetches internal metrics from a Logstash server. [Learn more]({learnMoreLink}).
home.tutorials.logstashMetrics.shortDesc: Fetch internal metrics from a Logstash server.
home.tutorials.memcachedMetrics.longDesc: The `memcached` Metricbeat module fetches internal metrics from Memcached. [Learn more]({learnMoreLink}).
home.tutorials.memcachedMetrics.shortDes: Fetch internal metrics from the Memcached server.
home.tutorials.microsoftLogs.longDescrip: Collect Microsoft Defender ATP alerts for use with Elastic Security. [Learn more]({learnMoreLink}).
home.tutorials.mispLogs.longDescription: This is a filebeat module for reading threat intel information from the MISP platform ( https://www.circl.lu/doc/misp/). It uses the httpjson input to access the MISP REST API interface. [Learn more]({learnMoreLink}).
home.tutorials.mispLogs.shortDescription: Collect MISP threat intelligence data with Filebeat.
home.tutorials.mongodbLogs.longDescripti: The  module collects and parses logs created by [MongoDB](https://www.mongodb.com/). [Learn more]({learnMoreLink}).
home.tutorials.mongodbMetrics.longDescri: The `mongodb` Metricbeat module fetches internal metrics from the MongoDB server. [Learn more]({learnMoreLink}).
home.tutorials.mssqlLogs.longDescription: The  module parses error logs created by MSSQL. [Learn more]({learnMoreLink}).
home.tutorials.mssqlMetrics.longDescript: The `mssql` Metricbeat module fetches monitoring, log and performance metrics from a Microsoft SQL Server instance. [Learn more]({learnMoreLink}).
home.tutorials.mssqlMetrics.shortDescrip: Fetch monitoring metrics from a Microsoft SQL Server instance
home.tutorials.muninMetrics.longDescript: The `munin` Metricbeat module fetches internal metrics from Munin. [Learn more]({learnMoreLink}).
home.tutorials.muninMetrics.shortDescrip: Fetch internal metrics from the Munin server.
home.tutorials.mysqlLogs.longDescription: The `mysql` Filebeat module parses error and slow logs created by MySQL. [Learn more]({learnMoreLink}).
home.tutorials.mysqlLogs.shortDescriptio: Collect and parse error and slow logs created by MySQL.
home.tutorials.mysqlMetrics.longDescript: The `mysql` Metricbeat module fetches internal metrics from the MySQL server. [Learn more]({learnMoreLink}).
home.tutorials.natsLogs.longDescription: The `nats` Filebeat module parses logs created by Nats. [Learn more]({learnMoreLink}).
home.tutorials.natsLogs.shortDescription: Collect and parse logs created by Nats.
home.tutorials.natsMetrics.longDescripti: The `nats` Metricbeat module fetches monitoring metrics from Nats. [Learn more]({learnMoreLink}).
home.tutorials.natsMetrics.shortDescript: Fetch monitoring metrics from the Nats server.
home.tutorials.netflowLogs.longDescripti: This is a module for receiving NetFlow and IPFIX flow records over UDP. This input supports NetFlow versions 1, 5, 6, 7, 8 and 9, as well as IPFIX. For NetFlow versions older than 9, fields are mapped automatically to NetFlow v9. [Learn more]({learnMoreLink}).
home.tutorials.netflowLogs.shortDescript: Collect NetFlow and IPFIX flow records.
home.tutorials.netscoutLogs.longDescript: This is a module for receiving Arbor Peakflow SP logs over Syslog or a file. [Learn more]({learnMoreLink}).
home.tutorials.netscoutLogs.shortDescrip: Collect Netscout Arbor Peakflow SP logs over syslog or from a file.
home.tutorials.nginxLogs.longDescription: The `nginx` Filebeat module parses access and error logs created by the Nginx HTTP server. [Learn more]({learnMoreLink}).
home.tutorials.nginxLogs.shortDescriptio: Collect and parse access and error logs created by the Nginx HTTP server.
home.tutorials.nginxMetrics.longDescript: The `nginx` Metricbeat module fetches internal metrics from the Nginx HTTP server. The module scrapes the server status data from the web page generated by the {statusModuleLink}, which must be enabled in your Nginx installation. [Learn more]({learnMoreLink}).
home.tutorials.nginxMetrics.shortDescrip: Fetch internal metrics from the Nginx HTTP server.
home.tutorials.o365Logs.longDescription: This is a module for Office 365 logs received via one of the Office 365         API endpoints. It currently supports user, admin, system, and policy         actions and events from Office 365 and Azure AD activity logs exposed         by the Office 365 Management Activity API.         [Learn more]({learnMoreLink}).
home.tutorials.o365Logs.shortDescription: Collect Office 365 activity logs via the Office 365 API.
home.tutorials.oktaLogs.longDescription: The Okta module collects events from the [Okta API](https://developer.okta.com/docs/reference/).         Specifically this supports reading from the [Okta System Log API](https://developer.okta.com/docs/reference/api/system-log/).         [Learn more]({learnMoreLink}).
home.tutorials.oktaLogs.shortDescription: Collect the Okta system log via the Okta API.
home.tutorials.openmetricsMetrics.longDe: The `openmetrics` Metricbeat module fetches metrics from an endpoint that serves metrics in OpenMetrics format. [Learn more]({learnMoreLink}).
home.tutorials.openmetricsMetrics.shortD: Fetch metrics from an endpoint that serves metrics in OpenMetrics format.
home.tutorials.oracleMetrics.longDescrip: The `{moduleName}` Metricbeat module fetches internal metrics from a Oracle server. [Learn more]({learnMoreLink}).
home.tutorials.oracleMetrics.shortDescri: Fetch internal metrics from a Oracle server.
home.tutorials.osqueryLogs.longDescripti: The  module collects and decodes the result logs written by         [osqueryd](https://osquery.readthedocs.io/en/latest/introduction/using-osqueryd/) in         the JSON format. To set up osqueryd follow the osquery installation instructions for         your operating system and configure the `filesystem` logging driver (the default).         Make sure UTC timestamps are enabled.         [Learn more]({learnMoreLink}).
home.tutorials.osqueryLogs.shortDescript: Collect osquery logs in JSON format.
home.tutorials.panwLogs.longDescription: This is a module for Palo Alto Networks PAN-OS firewall monitoring         logs received over Syslog or read from a file. It currently supports         messages of Traffic and Threat types. [Learn more]({learnMoreLink}).
home.tutorials.panwLogs.shortDescription: Collect Palo Alto Networks PAN-OS threat and traffic logs over syslog or from a log file.
home.tutorials.phpFpmMetrics.longDescrip: The `php_fpm` Metricbeat module fetches internal metrics from the PHP-FPM server. [Learn more]({learnMoreLink}).
home.tutorials.postgresqlLogs.longDescri: The `postgresql` Filebeat module parses error and slow logs created by PostgreSQL. [Learn more]({learnMoreLink}).
home.tutorials.postgresqlLogs.shortDescr: Collect and parse error and slow logs created by PostgreSQL.
home.tutorials.postgresqlMetrics.longDes: The `postgresql` Metricbeat module fetches internal metrics from the PostgreSQL server. [Learn more]({learnMoreLink}).
home.tutorials.prometheusMetrics.longDes: The `{moduleName}` Metricbeat module fetches metrics from Prometheus endpoint. [Learn more]({learnMoreLink}).
home.tutorials.prometheusMetrics.shortDe: Fetch metrics from a Prometheus exporter.
home.tutorials.rabbitmqLogs.longDescript: This is the module for parsing [RabbitMQ log files](https://www.rabbitmq.com/logging.html) [Learn more]({learnMoreLink}).
home.tutorials.rabbitmqMetrics.longDescr: The `rabbitmq` Metricbeat module fetches internal metrics from the RabbitMQ server. [Learn more]({learnMoreLink}).
home.tutorials.rabbitmqMetrics.shortDesc: Fetch internal metrics from the RabbitMQ server.
home.tutorials.radwareLogs.longDescripti: This is a module for receiving Radware DefensePro logs over Syslog or a file. [Learn more]({learnMoreLink}).
home.tutorials.radwareLogs.shortDescript: Collect Radware DefensePro logs over syslog or from a file.
home.tutorials.redisLogs.longDescription: The `redis` Filebeat module parses error and slow logs created by Redis. For Redis to write error logs, make sure the `logfile` option, from the Redis configuration file, is set to `redis-server.log`. The slow logs are read directly from Redis via the `SLOWLOG` command. For Redis to record slow logs, make sure the `slowlog-log-slower-than` option is set. Note that the `slowlog` fileset is experimental. [Learn more]({learnMoreLink}).
home.tutorials.redisLogs.shortDescriptio: Collect and parse error and slow logs created by Redis.
home.tutorials.redisMetrics.longDescript: The `redis` Metricbeat module fetches internal metrics from the Redis server. [Learn more]({learnMoreLink}).
home.tutorials.redisenterpriseMetrics.lo: The `redisenterprise` Metricbeat module fetches monitoring metrics from Redis Enterprise Server [Learn more]({learnMoreLink}).
home.tutorials.redisenterpriseMetrics.sh: Fetch monitoring metrics from Redis Enterprise Server.
home.tutorials.santaLogs.longDescription: The  module collects and parses logs from [Google Santa](https://github.com/google/santa),         a security tool for macOS that monitors process executions and can blacklist/whitelist binaries. [Learn more]({learnMoreLink}).
home.tutorials.santaLogs.shortDescriptio: Collect Google Santa logs about process executions on MacOS.
home.tutorials.sonicwallLogs.longDescrip: This is a module for receiving Sonicwall-FW logs over Syslog or a file. [Learn more]({learnMoreLink}).
home.tutorials.sonicwallLogs.shortDescri: Collect Sonicwall-FW logs over syslog or from a file.
home.tutorials.sophosLogs.longDescriptio: This is a module for Sophos Products, currently it supports XG SFOS logs sent in the syslog format. [Learn more]({learnMoreLink}).
home.tutorials.sophosLogs.shortDescripti: Collect Sophos XG SFOS logs over syslog.
home.tutorials.squidLogs.longDescription: This is a module for receiving Squid logs over Syslog or a file. [Learn more]({learnMoreLink}).
home.tutorials.squidLogs.shortDescriptio: Collect Squid logs over syslog or from a file.
home.tutorials.stanMetrics.longDescripti: The `stan` Metricbeat module fetches monitoring metrics from STAN. [Learn more]({learnMoreLink}).
home.tutorials.stanMetrics.shortDescript: Fetch monitoring metrics from the STAN server.
home.tutorials.statsdMetrics.longDescrip: The `statsd` Metricbeat module fetches monitoring metrics from statsd. [Learn more]({learnMoreLink}).
home.tutorials.suricataLogs.longDescript: This is a module to the Suricata IDS/IPS/NSM log. It parses logs that are         in the [Suricata Eve JSON format](https://suricata.readthedocs.io/en/latest/output/eve/eve-json-format.html).         [Learn more]({learnMoreLink}).
home.tutorials.systemLogs.longDescriptio: The  module collects and parses logs created by the system logging service of common Unix/Linux based distributions. [Learn more]({learnMoreLink}).
home.tutorials.systemLogs.shortDescripti: Collect system logs of common Unix/Linux based distributions.
home.tutorials.systemMetrics.longDescrip: The `system` Metricbeat module collects CPU, memory, network, and disk statistics from the host. It collects system wide statistics and statistics per process and filesystem. [Learn more]({learnMoreLink}).
home.tutorials.systemMetrics.shortDescri: Collect CPU, memory, network, and disk statistics from the host.
home.tutorials.tomcatLogs.longDescriptio: This is a module for receiving Apache Tomcat logs over Syslog or a file. [Learn more]({learnMoreLink}).
home.tutorials.tomcatLogs.shortDescripti: Collect Apache Tomcat logs over syslog or from a file.
home.tutorials.traefikLogs.longDescripti: The  module parses access logs created by [Træfik](https://traefik.io/). [Learn more]({learnMoreLink}).
home.tutorials.traefikMetrics.longDescri: The `traefik` Metricbeat module fetches monitoring metrics from Traefik. [Learn more]({learnMoreLink}).
home.tutorials.uptimeMonitors.longDescri: Monitor services for their availability with active probing.         Given a list of URLs, Heartbeat asks the simple question: Are you alive?         [Learn more]({learnMoreLink}).
home.tutorials.uwsgiMetrics.longDescript: The `uwsgi` Metricbeat module fetches internal metrics from the uWSGI server. [Learn more]({learnMoreLink}).
home.tutorials.uwsgiMetrics.shortDescrip: Fetch internal metrics from the uWSGI server.
home.tutorials.vsphereMetrics.longDescri: The `vsphere` Metricbeat module fetches internal metrics from a vSphere cluster. [Learn more]({learnMoreLink}).
home.tutorials.windowsEventLogs.longDesc: Use Winlogbeat to collect the logs from the Windows Event Log. [Learn more]({learnMoreLink}).
home.tutorials.windowsEventLogs.shortDes: Fetch logs from the Windows Event Log.
home.tutorials.windowsMetrics.longDescri: The `windows` Metricbeat module fetches internal metrics from Windows. [Learn more]({learnMoreLink}).
home.tutorials.zeekLogs.longDescription: This is a module for Zeek, which used to be called Bro. It parses logs         that are in the [Zeek JSON format](https://www.zeek.org/manual/release/logs/index.html).         [Learn more]({learnMoreLink}).
home.tutorials.zeekLogs.shortDescription: Collect Zeek network security monitoring logs.
home.tutorials.zookeeperMetrics.longDesc: The `{moduleName}` Metricbeat module fetches internal metrics from a Zookeeper server. [Learn more]({learnMoreLink}).
home.tutorials.zookeeperMetrics.shortDes: Fetch internal metrics from a Zookeeper server.
home.tutorials.zscalerLogs.longDescripti: This is a module for receiving Zscaler NSS logs over Syslog or a file. [Learn more]({learnMoreLink}).
home.tutorials.zscalerLogs.shortDescript: This is a module for receiving Zscaler NSS logs over Syslog or a file.
